<br>
<big>24.1&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Use of the dative case</big><br>
<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;This case is used to signify indirect objects, and
is also used by certain prepositions.&nbsp; Very often, words in the
dative case can be translated into English as having the word ‘to’
placed before them.&nbsp; There are also certain constructions with
predicates that use the dative case.<br>
<br>
